<PageTitle>Section 2: Composition of the Committee</PageTitle>

<div class="discipline-content">
    <div class="content-header">
        <h1>Section 2: Composition of the Committee</h1>
        <p class="section-subtitle">DepEd School Discipline Rules of Procedure</p>
    </div>

    <div class="content-body">
        <div class="section-card">
            <h2>2.1 Committee Members</h2>
            <p>The School Discipline Committee shall be composed of the following members:</p>
            
            <div class="highlight-box">
                <h3>Core Members (Required)</h3>
                <ul>
                    <li><strong>School Principal</strong> - Chairperson</li>
                    <li><strong>Guidance Counselor</strong> - Vice Chairperson</li>
                    <li><strong>Prefect of Discipline</strong> - Secretary</li>
                    <li><strong>Two (2) Teachers</strong> - Members (elected by faculty)</li>
                    <li><strong>One (1) Student Representative</strong> - Member (elected by student body)</li>
                </ul>
            </div>

            <h2>2.2 Additional Members (Optional)</h2>
            <p>Depending on the school size and complexity, the committee may include:</p>
            <ul>
                <li>Parent-Teacher Association (PTA) Representative</li>
                <li>School Nurse or Health Personnel</li>
                <li>Security Personnel (for security-related cases)</li>
                <li>External Counselor (for serious cases)</li>
            </ul>

            <h2>2.3 Selection Criteria</h2>
            <div class="info-box">
                <h3>For Teacher Members:</h3>
                <ul>
                    <li>Must have at least 3 years of teaching experience</li>
                    <li>Must have completed child protection training</li>
                    <li>Must demonstrate fairness and impartiality</li>
                    <li>Must have good communication skills</li>
                </ul>
            </div>

            <div class="info-box">
                <h3>For Student Representative:</h3>
                <ul>
                    <li>Must be in good academic standing</li>
                    <li>Must have no disciplinary record</li>
                    <li>Must be elected by the student body</li>
                    <li>Must be at least 15 years old (for secondary schools)</li>
                </ul>
            </div>

            <h2>2.4 Term of Office</h2>
            <p>The committee members shall serve for a term of:</p>
            <ul>
                <li><strong>Principal and Guidance Counselor:</strong> Ex-officio (permanent)</li>
                <li><strong>Teachers:</strong> Two (2) years, renewable</li>
                <li><strong>Student Representative:</strong> One (1) year</li>
                <li><strong>Other Members:</strong> As determined by the school</li>
            </ul>

            <h2>2.5 Roles and Responsibilities</h2>
            <div class="highlight-box">
                <h3>Chairperson (Principal)</h3>
                <ul>
                    <li>Presides over all committee meetings</li>
                    <li>Ensures proper implementation of decisions</li>
                    <li>Represents the school in external communications</li>
                    <li>Approves final disciplinary actions</li>
                </ul>
            </div>

            <div class="highlight-box">
                <h3>Vice Chairperson (Guidance Counselor)</h3>
                <ul>
                    <li>Assists the chairperson in all functions</li>
                    <li>Provides psychological assessment when needed</li>
                    <li>Coordinates with external agencies</li>
                    <li>Monitors student welfare during proceedings</li>
                </ul>
            </div>

            <div class="highlight-box">
                <h3>Secretary (Prefect of Discipline)</h3>
                <ul>
                    <li>Records all committee proceedings</li>
                    <li>Maintains case files and documentation</li>
                    <li>Coordinates with teachers and staff</li>
                    <li>Implements approved disciplinary measures</li>
                </ul>
            </div>
        </div>
    </div>
</div>

